      "content": "but it wasnt just a \"pattern\" though. the movements were identical. like, he tripped on the same crack in the sidewalk at the exact same time. it felt less like my brain playing tricks and more like the world just... repeated itself. if it's not a glitch, why does it feel like the environment is just being recycled because it's too hard to render everything fresh? doesn't that make sense from a computational standpoint?",
